Coat the salmon slices in the sesame seeds.Heat the oil in a frying pan over a medium heat. Add the salmon and fry for 3-4 minutes on each side, or until cooked through and golden-brown on both sides.Add the coriander, dill, orange juice and soy sauce and continue to cook for 2-3 minutes, until the sauce is bubbling.To serve, place the sesame-crusted salmon pieces onto a serving plate, spoon the orange and soy sauce over the fish, and garnish with the orange segments.